---
import '../styles/custom.css'
const title = 'Vectis Mail — Self-Hosted Email Platform'
const description = 'Containerised, self-hosted email server with declarative config, sending API, admin dashboard, and enterprise features. Deploy in minutes.'
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8" />
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
	<title>{title}</title>
	<meta name="description" content={description} />
	<meta property="og:title" content={title} />
	<meta property="og:description" content={description} />
	<meta property="og:type" content="website" />
	<meta property="og:url" content="https://vectismail.com" />
	<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
</head>
<body class="marketing-page">
	<nav class="marketing-nav">
		<a href="/" class="logo"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="Vectis Mail" height="26" /></a>
		<div>
			<a href="/features">Features</a>
			<a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
			<a href="/getting-started">Docs</a>
			<a href="/about">About</a>
			<a href="/contact">Contact</a>
		</div>
	</nav>

	<div class="hero-wrapper">
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="hero-badge">Open Source &middot; Self-Hosted &middot; API-First</div>
			<h1>Your email server.<br/><span>Your rules.</span></h1>
			<p>Deploy a production mail server in minutes. Declarative config, transactional sending API, inbound webhooks, and a full admin dashboard — all in one platform.</p>
			<div class="hero-buttons">
				<a href="/getting-started/installation" class="btn-primary">Get Started Free</a>
				<a href="/getting-started" class="btn-secondary">Read the Docs</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<div class="stats-bar">
		<div class="stat-item">
			<div class="stat-number">9</div>
			<div class="stat-label">Containers, One Config</div>
		</div>
		<div class="stat-item">
			<div class="stat-number">60+</div>
			<div class="stat-label">API Endpoints</div>
		</div>
		<div class="stat-item">
			<div class="stat-number">22</div>
			<div class="stat-label">Doc Pages</div>
		</div>
		<div class="stat-item">
			<div class="stat-number">3</div>
			<div class="stat-label">Pricing Tiers</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Everything you need for production email</h2>
		<p class="subtitle">Postfix, Dovecot, Rspamd, DKIM, SPF, DMARC — configured and managed through a single YAML file.</p>
		<div class="feature-grid">
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-blue">&#9881;</div>
				<h3>Declarative Configuration</h3>
				<p>One config.yaml defines your entire mail stack. Change a setting, run apply, and Vectis generates Postfix, Dovecot, Rspamd, and Traefik configs automatically.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-cyan">&#9889;</div>
				<h3>Sending API</h3>
				<p>REST API for transactional email. Single and batch sending, domain-scoped API keys, webhook callbacks for delivery status. Drop-in replacement for external email services.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-purple">&#9638;</div>
				<h3>Admin Dashboard</h3>
				<p>Full web UI for domains, mailboxes, aliases, deliverability, audit logs, backups, and system updates. Role-based access control with TOTP MFA and OIDC SSO.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-green">&#10548;</div>
				<h3>Inbound Webhooks</h3>
				<p>Receive email programmatically. Vectis parses inbound messages and POSTs the full content — body, attachments, headers, envelope — to your application via HMAC-signed webhooks.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-blue">&#128274;</div>
				<h3>Automatic TLS</h3>
				<p>Let's Encrypt certificates provisioned and renewed automatically via acme.sh. Supports Cloudflare DNS-01 challenges. TLS 1.2+ enforced on all protocols.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-orange">&#128200;</div>
				<h3>Built-in Observability</h3>
				<p>Prometheus metrics, Grafana dashboards, Loki log aggregation, per-domain analytics, IP warmup tracking, and RBL monitoring — all included.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-green">&#8635;</div>
				<h3>Atomic Updates</h3>
				<p>The orchestrator manages updates with a 6-phase pipeline: snapshot, migrate, pull, deploy, health check, complete. Automatic rollback on failure.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-purple">&#9993;</div>
				<h3>Webmail Included</h3>
				<p>Roundcube webmail with ManageSieve filter rules, mobile-responsive Elastic skin, and Vectis branding. Your users get a familiar email experience out of the box.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="icon icon-cyan">&#11036;</div>
				<h3>Clustering &amp; HA</h3>
				<p>Multi-node clustering with leader election, rolling updates, PgBouncer connection pooling, and cross-node health checking for high-availability deployments.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="cta-section">
		<h2>Trusted by the Veltara Works ecosystem</h2>
		<p>Vectis Mail powers transactional email for <a href="https://validonx.com" style="color: var(--vm-blue);">ValidonX</a> and other Veltara Works products.</p>
		<div class="hero-buttons">
			<a href="/pricing" class="btn-primary">View Pricing</a>
			<a href="https://github.com/Veltara-Works/vectis" class="btn-secondary">GitHub</a>
		</div>
	</div>

	<footer class="footer">
		<span>&copy; 2026 Veltara Works. All rights reserved.</span>
		<div>
			<a href="/getting-started">Docs</a> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
			<a href="https://github.com/Veltara-Works/vectis">GitHub</a> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
			<a href="/contact">Contact</a>
		</div>
	</footer>
</body>
</html>
